President Barack Obama has announced the continuation of the national emergency with respect to the situation in or in relation to the Democratic Republic of the Congo. This declaration, made in accordance with Section 202(d) of the National Emergencies Act, states that the situation in the country continues to pose an unusual and extraordinary threat to the foreign policy of the United States. The violence and atrocities in the Democratic Republic of the Congo have been ongoing and have the potential to destabilize the region. Therefore, President Obama has determined it necessary to extend the national emergency declared in Executive Order 13413 beyond its original expiration date of October 27, 2015.